2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the construction of spanning trees in a network, which is a networking concept. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a scheme for optimizing tree metrics, which is a topic in data structures and algorithms. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the design of a protocol for constructing spanning trees, which can be seen as a control problem in a distributed system. 
5. cs.AL (Computational Geometry) - The paper deals with the optimization of tree metrics, which can be seen as a computational geometry problem.
